HEADWORD: Fracas
<hw>Fra"cas</hw> <pr>(fr⟦amac⟧"k⟦ait⟧s; F. fr⟦adot⟧`k⟦aum⟧"; 277)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., crash, din, tumult, It. <ets>fracasso</ets>, fr.
<ets>fracassare</ets> to break in pieces, perh. fr. <ets>fra</ets>
within, among (L. <ets>infra</ets>) + <ets>cassare</ets> to annul,
cashier. Cf. <er>Cashier</er>, <pos>v. t.</pos>]</ety> <def>An uproar; a
noisy quarrel; a disturbance; a brawl.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

